WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.445 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:02.445 --> 00:00:14.670 align:middle line:90%


00:00:14.670 --> 00:00:16.590 align:middle line:90%
>> Fumbled across in practice.

00:00:16.590 --> 00:00:19.720 align:middle line:84%
So I was looking for better
solutions for heart disease.

00:00:19.720 --> 00:00:21.990 align:middle line:84%
My mom died of
sudden cardiac death.

00:00:21.990 --> 00:00:23.430 align:middle line:84%
She died a couple
of months after

00:00:23.430 --> 00:00:25.680 align:middle line:90%
her two-vessel angioplasty.

00:00:25.680 --> 00:00:26.700 align:middle line:90%
And that's what I did.

00:00:26.700 --> 00:00:28.590 align:middle line:90%
That's what I did in my career.

00:00:28.590 --> 00:00:30.810 align:middle line:84%
I spent morning till night
working in the cath lab,

00:00:30.810 --> 00:00:32.820 align:middle line:84%
where we did heart
catheterizations

00:00:32.820 --> 00:00:34.710 align:middle line:84%
and certain stents
and angioplasty,

00:00:34.710 --> 00:00:36.600 align:middle line:90%
those kinds of procedures.

00:00:36.600 --> 00:00:39.030 align:middle line:84%
And my own mother dies
a couple of months

00:00:39.030 --> 00:00:41.310 align:middle line:84%
after her procedure
in New Jersey.

00:00:41.310 --> 00:00:44.640 align:middle line:84%
Well, it got me thinking that
there were better answers than

00:00:44.640 --> 00:00:47.430 align:middle line:84%
just having people come to a
hospital-- a procedure room,

00:00:47.430 --> 00:00:48.480 align:middle line:90%
a cath lab--

00:00:48.480 --> 00:00:51.690 align:middle line:84%
and then send them on their way
with their statin cholesterol

00:00:51.690 --> 00:00:55.440 align:middle line:84%
drug, advised to cut their fat,
eat more healthy whole grains.

00:00:55.440 --> 00:00:56.520 align:middle line:90%
And they're back.

00:00:56.520 --> 00:00:59.800 align:middle line:84%
So those efforts do not
put a stop to this disease,

00:00:59.800 --> 00:01:01.020 align:middle line:90%
nor do they even slow it.

00:01:01.020 --> 00:01:04.050 align:middle line:84%
They have a very
minor effect, if any.

00:01:04.050 --> 00:01:05.040 align:middle line:90%
It's an odd thing.

00:01:05.040 --> 00:01:07.860 align:middle line:84%
The pharmaceutical industry
has turned cholesterol

00:01:07.860 --> 00:01:10.080 align:middle line:90%
into a huge revenue opportunity.

00:01:10.080 --> 00:01:13.230 align:middle line:84%
And it has very little
effect, to reduce cholesterol,

00:01:13.230 --> 00:01:15.370 align:middle line:90%
on reducing cardiovascular risk.

00:01:15.370 --> 00:01:16.707 align:middle line:90%
So I tried to find better ways.

00:01:16.707 --> 00:01:17.790 align:middle line:90%
I was seeking better ways.

00:01:17.790 --> 00:01:20.460 align:middle line:84%
You have to start looking
really hard for those answers,

00:01:20.460 --> 00:01:23.100 align:middle line:84%
because those answers
are just not out there.

00:01:23.100 --> 00:01:25.980 align:middle line:84%
Well, the number one cause,
the most common cause

00:01:25.980 --> 00:01:27.660 align:middle line:90%
for a heart attack--

00:01:27.660 --> 00:01:31.300 align:middle line:84%
needing stents, bypass surgery,
those sorts of things--

00:01:31.300 --> 00:01:33.960 align:middle line:84%
the most common abnormality
is not high cholesterol.

00:01:33.960 --> 00:01:36.600 align:middle line:84%
I call that the kindergarten
version of heart disease

00:01:36.600 --> 00:01:37.530 align:middle line:90%
causation.

00:01:37.530 --> 00:01:42.960 align:middle line:84%
The most common cause is an
excess of small LDL particles.

00:01:42.960 --> 00:01:44.310 align:middle line:90%
It's called LDL cholesterol.

00:01:44.310 --> 00:01:46.530 align:middle line:84%
But that's a really
dumbed-down version.

00:01:46.530 --> 00:01:49.680 align:middle line:84%
It's an excess of small
LDL particles coupled

00:01:49.680 --> 00:01:52.240 align:middle line:84%
with some other things, such
as inflammation and high blood

00:01:52.240 --> 00:01:53.040 align:middle line:90%
sugars--

00:01:53.040 --> 00:01:55.180 align:middle line:90%
very, very common abnormalities.

00:01:55.180 --> 00:01:56.640 align:middle line:84%
So I set out to
try to find better

00:01:56.640 --> 00:02:00.600 align:middle line:84%
solutions for my patients at
very large cardiology practice.

00:02:00.600 --> 00:02:02.070 align:middle line:84%
And I saw what
happened to people

00:02:02.070 --> 00:02:03.240 align:middle line:90%
who needed these procedures.

00:02:03.240 --> 00:02:04.468 align:middle line:90%
And some die.

00:02:04.468 --> 00:02:05.760 align:middle line:90%
It can be a fatal disease, too.

00:02:05.760 --> 00:02:07.280 align:middle line:90%
It's not a funny business.

00:02:07.280 --> 00:02:09.750 align:middle line:90%
It's not a light matter.

00:02:09.750 --> 00:02:11.910 align:middle line:84%
Well, there's only
two things that

00:02:11.910 --> 00:02:15.870 align:middle line:84%
cause an excess of small LDL
particles, that leads to heart

00:02:15.870 --> 00:02:17.280 align:middle line:90%
attack and heart disease.

00:02:17.280 --> 00:02:20.068 align:middle line:90%
And that's grains and sugars--

00:02:20.068 --> 00:02:21.360 align:middle line:90%
not my speculation, by the way.

00:02:21.360 --> 00:02:23.730 align:middle line:84%
This science is quite
well sorted out.

00:02:23.730 --> 00:02:25.730 align:middle line:84%
It's been sorted out
for over 20 years.

00:02:25.730 --> 00:02:27.300 align:middle line:90%
But it's not talked about much.

00:02:27.300 --> 00:02:29.190 align:middle line:84%
My cynical view is it's
not talked about much

00:02:29.190 --> 00:02:32.120 align:middle line:84%
because there's no pot of
gold for the treatment.

00:02:32.120 --> 00:02:35.310 align:middle line:84%
It's treated, it's corrected--
not by a little bit,

00:02:35.310 --> 00:02:36.600 align:middle line:90%
but entirely--

00:02:36.600 --> 00:02:39.840 align:middle line:84%
in the majority of people by
eliminating those two causes.

00:02:39.840 --> 00:02:43.740 align:middle line:84%
No grains, no sugars,
and small LDL plummets.

00:02:43.740 --> 00:02:46.718 align:middle line:84%
A typical measure would be
1,800 nanomoles per liter.

00:02:46.718 --> 00:02:47.760 align:middle line:90%
That's how it's measured.

00:02:47.760 --> 00:02:49.500 align:middle line:84%
It's a particle
count per volume.

00:02:49.500 --> 00:02:53.010 align:middle line:84%
It drops to zero, or
some other low number.

00:02:53.010 --> 00:02:54.310 align:middle line:90%
It's not a little bit better.

00:02:54.310 --> 00:02:55.620 align:middle line:90%
It's a ton better.

00:02:55.620 --> 00:02:57.400 align:middle line:90%
And you do it for free.

00:02:57.400 --> 00:02:59.550 align:middle line:90%
So I did this in my patients.

00:02:59.550 --> 00:03:03.450 align:middle line:84%
To my great surprise-- so I
watched their small LDL values

00:03:03.450 --> 00:03:05.202 align:middle line:90%
plummet, as you'd expect.

00:03:05.202 --> 00:03:06.660 align:middle line:84%
I watched other
good things happen,

00:03:06.660 --> 00:03:09.630 align:middle line:84%
like triglyceride levels
drop and blood sugar drop.

00:03:09.630 --> 00:03:12.930 align:middle line:84%
But people came back me and
said, I don't understand.

00:03:12.930 --> 00:03:15.360 align:middle line:90%
Why did I lose 57 pounds?

00:03:15.360 --> 00:03:16.350 align:middle line:90%
I didn't try.

00:03:16.350 --> 00:03:17.440 align:middle line:90%
I didn't exercise.

00:03:17.440 --> 00:03:18.630 align:middle line:90%
I didn't cut my calories.

00:03:18.630 --> 00:03:19.590 align:middle line:90%
I didn't cut my fat.

00:03:19.590 --> 00:03:21.450 align:middle line:84%
In fact, you told
me to eat more fat!

00:03:21.450 --> 00:03:23.640 align:middle line:90%
And don't push the plate away.

00:03:23.640 --> 00:03:25.830 align:middle line:84%
Why did my rheumatoid
arthritis go away?

00:03:25.830 --> 00:03:28.620 align:middle line:84%
Why did my ulcerative colitis,
that plagued me for years

00:03:28.620 --> 00:03:32.100 align:middle line:84%
and led to bloody diarrhea
and I needed transfusions

00:03:32.100 --> 00:03:34.530 align:middle line:84%
every few months,
why did it stop?

00:03:34.530 --> 00:03:36.110 align:middle line:90%
Why did my mind fog lift?

00:03:36.110 --> 00:03:38.610 align:middle line:84%
Why did my migraines headaches,
that I had five times a week

00:03:38.610 --> 00:03:41.040 align:middle line:84%
that were crippling and I
had to take multiple drugs,

00:03:41.040 --> 00:03:43.330 align:middle line:90%
go away after just a week?

00:03:43.330 --> 00:03:45.968 align:middle line:84%
Why is my acid reflux
now gone after five days?

00:03:45.968 --> 00:03:47.760 align:middle line:84%
Why is my irritable
bowel syndrome symptoms

00:03:47.760 --> 00:03:49.290 align:middle line:90%
gone within the first week?

00:03:49.290 --> 00:03:53.810 align:middle line:84%
So I experienced this outpouring
of incredible stories.

00:03:53.810 --> 00:03:57.340 align:middle line:84%
And my first response
was, I don't know.

00:03:57.340 --> 00:04:00.210 align:middle line:84%
I have no idea why you had these
transformations in your health

00:04:00.210 --> 00:04:01.560 align:middle line:90%
and appearance.

00:04:01.560 --> 00:04:04.620 align:middle line:84%
But it became clear on a
large basis, face-to-face

00:04:04.620 --> 00:04:08.580 align:middle line:84%
in my practice, that there
was something fishy going on.

00:04:08.580 --> 00:04:10.378 align:middle line:84%
So I decided to
try to understand.

00:04:10.378 --> 00:04:11.670 align:middle line:90%
What in the world was going on?

00:04:11.670 --> 00:04:13.620 align:middle line:84%
I eliminated the
foods that we're told

00:04:13.620 --> 00:04:17.029 align:middle line:84%
should dominate the
diet, right, a diet

00:04:17.029 --> 00:04:18.720 align:middle line:90%
centered on whole grains.

00:04:18.720 --> 00:04:20.760 align:middle line:84%
We're told now that
70% of all calories

00:04:20.760 --> 00:04:23.770 align:middle line:84%
should come from grains,
preferably whole grains.

00:04:23.770 --> 00:04:25.140 align:middle line:90%
So we're told to eat this food.

00:04:25.140 --> 00:04:29.110 align:middle line:84%
When you take it out, all
these incredible things happen.

00:04:29.110 --> 00:04:30.480 align:middle line:90%
So I started to dig.

00:04:30.480 --> 00:04:34.650 align:middle line:84%
Why would removing the food
that is the darling of the US

00:04:34.650 --> 00:04:37.230 align:middle line:84%
dietary guidelines for
Americans, The American Heart

00:04:37.230 --> 00:04:42.210 align:middle line:84%
Association, its counterparts
in Australia and the UK,

00:04:42.210 --> 00:04:45.210 align:middle line:84%
the favorite of the American
Diabetes Association,

00:04:45.210 --> 00:04:47.528 align:middle line:84%
the thing that's held
up as a perfect food

00:04:47.528 --> 00:04:49.320 align:middle line:84%
by the Academy of
Nutrition and Dietetics--

00:04:49.320 --> 00:04:52.180 align:middle line:84%
we take that food out and
wonderful things happen.

00:04:52.180 --> 00:04:52.980 align:middle line:90%
But why?

00:04:52.980 --> 00:04:53.940 align:middle line:90%
What happened in this thing?

00:04:53.940 --> 00:04:55.830 align:middle line:84%
And that's when I
started to poke around--

00:04:55.830 --> 00:04:59.430 align:middle line:84%
into agribusiness and
agricultural genetics-- to see,

00:04:59.430 --> 00:05:03.240 align:middle line:84%
what happened to
wheat, in particular?

00:05:03.240 --> 00:05:04.800 align:middle line:90%
This applies to more than wheat.

00:05:04.800 --> 00:05:06.030 align:middle line:90%
But I picked on wheat.

00:05:06.030 --> 00:05:08.790 align:middle line:90%
I call it the ring leader.

00:05:08.790 --> 00:05:14.050 align:middle line:84%
It's the worst of the
worst among all grains.

00:05:14.050 --> 00:05:16.470 align:middle line:84%
Well, digging, it
became clear that what

00:05:16.470 --> 00:05:18.740 align:middle line:84%
we're being sold
today as modern wheat

00:05:18.740 --> 00:05:22.600 align:middle line:84%
is something entirely different
than what it was 40 years ago.

00:05:22.600 --> 00:05:24.410 align:middle line:84%
So there was a
very noble effort--

00:05:24.410 --> 00:05:29.700 align:middle line:84%
not a dishonest or evil
effort, but a noble effort

00:05:29.700 --> 00:05:32.500 align:middle line:84%
to increase the yield per
acre to help feed the world's

00:05:32.500 --> 00:05:33.300 align:middle line:90%
hungry.

00:05:33.300 --> 00:05:34.660 align:middle line:90%
A noble effort.

00:05:34.660 --> 00:05:38.190 align:middle line:84%
But in those efforts,
they bred wheat

00:05:38.190 --> 00:05:40.380 align:middle line:84%
over and over and over
again, with various strains.

00:05:40.380 --> 00:05:41.460 align:middle line:90%
They bred wheat.

00:05:41.460 --> 00:05:43.080 align:middle line:90%
Wheat is a grass.

00:05:43.080 --> 00:05:46.530 align:middle line:84%
They bred wheat with
other wild grasses

00:05:46.530 --> 00:05:50.080 align:middle line:84%
to extract certain
genetic characteristics.

00:05:50.080 --> 00:05:53.290 align:middle line:84%
And then they started to
subject wheat to other methods,

00:05:53.290 --> 00:05:55.950 align:middle line:84%
such as the methods
of mutagenesis,

00:05:55.950 --> 00:05:58.500 align:middle line:84%
the purposeful
induction of mutations

00:05:58.500 --> 00:06:01.170 align:middle line:84%
using toxic
chemicals, radiation,

00:06:01.170 --> 00:06:03.600 align:middle line:90%
gamma rays, et cetera.

00:06:03.600 --> 00:06:07.070 align:middle line:84%
Problem-- you can't control
the mutations you get.

00:06:07.070 --> 00:06:09.300 align:middle line:84%
You can't order up
the mutation you want,

00:06:09.300 --> 00:06:11.910 align:middle line:84%
say for better pest
resistance or reduced height.

00:06:11.910 --> 00:06:15.150 align:middle line:84%
You just get dozens, perhaps
hundreds of mutations.

00:06:15.150 --> 00:06:17.340 align:middle line:84%
If they're not fatal,
the plant survives.

00:06:17.340 --> 00:06:19.025 align:middle line:84%
But you've induced
numerous mutations.

00:06:19.025 --> 00:06:20.400 align:middle line:84%
And by the way,
this all occurred

00:06:20.400 --> 00:06:23.130 align:middle line:84%
prior to the age of
genetic modification,

00:06:23.130 --> 00:06:24.030 align:middle line:90%
genetic engineering.

00:06:24.030 --> 00:06:25.980 align:middle line:84%
And I point that out
because agribusiness,

00:06:25.980 --> 00:06:27.653 align:middle line:84%
who does not like
me very much, says

00:06:27.653 --> 00:06:29.820 align:middle line:84%
there's no such thing as
genetically modified wheat.

00:06:29.820 --> 00:06:31.060 align:middle line:90%
Davis is wrong.

00:06:31.060 --> 00:06:32.610 align:middle line:90%
No, there is no such thing as--

00:06:32.610 --> 00:06:34.080 align:middle line:90%
that's right.

00:06:34.080 --> 00:06:37.290 align:middle line:84%
Wheat was changed by methods
that pre-date genetic

00:06:37.290 --> 00:06:39.450 align:middle line:84%
modification, which
in many instances

00:06:39.450 --> 00:06:42.450 align:middle line:84%
are far worse than
genetic modification.

00:06:42.450 --> 00:06:45.000 align:middle line:84%
I'm no defender of
genetic modification.

00:06:45.000 --> 00:06:47.100 align:middle line:84%
I think it's an awful
practice, or at least

00:06:47.100 --> 00:06:49.410 align:middle line:90%
the current versions are.

00:06:49.410 --> 00:06:51.300 align:middle line:84%
But believe it or not,
it's an improvement

00:06:51.300 --> 00:06:54.310 align:middle line:84%
over the methods that were
used to generate modern wheat.

00:06:54.310 --> 00:06:55.530 align:middle line:90%
So wheat is now--

00:06:55.530 --> 00:06:58.550 align:middle line:84%
it's no longer a 4 and 1/2
foot, five foot tall, two

00:06:58.550 --> 00:06:59.675 align:middle line:90%
meter tall--

00:06:59.675 --> 00:07:01.170 align:middle line:90%
nearly two meter tall--

00:07:01.170 --> 00:07:02.580 align:middle line:90%
traditional plant.

00:07:02.580 --> 00:07:09.270 align:middle line:84%
It's an 18-inch tall, short,
thick, stocky, semi-dwarf

00:07:09.270 --> 00:07:10.540 align:middle line:90%
strain, they call it.

00:07:10.540 --> 00:07:12.750 align:middle line:84%
So that change in
appearance is accompanied

00:07:12.750 --> 00:07:16.620 align:middle line:84%
by multiple changes in its
genetics, in it's biochemistry,

00:07:16.620 --> 00:07:19.050 align:middle line:84%
and the proteins, in
particular, that are expressed.

00:07:19.050 --> 00:07:23.190 align:middle line:84%
And when products
made with high-yield,

00:07:23.190 --> 00:07:25.200 align:middle line:84%
semi-dwarf wheat were
put on store shelves

00:07:25.200 --> 00:07:28.800 align:middle line:84%
around 1985, the
late '80s, that's

00:07:28.800 --> 00:07:32.030 align:middle line:84%
when we saw an explosion
in numerous problems.

00:07:32.030 --> 00:07:34.380 align:middle line:84%
Now, that doesn't
prove cause and effect.

00:07:34.380 --> 00:07:37.450 align:middle line:84%
But I'm pretty well convinced it
is probably a cause and effect,

00:07:37.450 --> 00:07:41.580 align:middle line:84%
because it coincides perfectly
with a dramatic increase

00:07:41.580 --> 00:07:47.100 align:middle line:84%
in calorie intake in Australia,
the US, Western Europe, UK.

00:07:47.100 --> 00:07:49.770 align:middle line:84%
It coincides perfectly
with an explosion

00:07:49.770 --> 00:07:54.980 align:middle line:84%
in autoimmune diseases and in
type 2 diabetes and obesity,

00:07:54.980 --> 00:08:00.420 align:middle line:84%
and because we see all those
conditions reverse promptly

00:08:00.420 --> 00:08:02.440 align:middle line:90%
with grain elimination.

00:08:02.440 --> 00:08:06.000 align:middle line:84%
So a lot of the problems arose
from these changes introduced

00:08:06.000 --> 00:08:09.120 align:middle line:84%
into wheat-- and, to some
degree, other related grains,

00:08:09.120 --> 00:08:11.763 align:middle line:84%
too, though wheat being
the worst of the worst.

00:08:11.763 --> 00:08:14.178 align:middle line:90%
