00:08:14.178 --> 00:08:18.970 align:middle line:90%


00:08:18.970 --> 00:08:19.770 align:middle line:90%
Sure.

00:08:19.770 --> 00:08:22.620 align:middle line:84%
Even if viewers don't
accept this notion

00:08:22.620 --> 00:08:25.948 align:middle line:84%
that there are unique proteins
created in modern wheat,

00:08:25.948 --> 00:08:27.490 align:middle line:84%
like gliadin, wheat
germ and gluten--

00:08:27.490 --> 00:08:29.850 align:middle line:84%
there's a whole question
of toxic proteins.

00:08:29.850 --> 00:08:33.570 align:middle line:84%
Even if we put all that aside,
there was the inarguable--

00:08:33.570 --> 00:08:35.640 align:middle line:90%
I wish I could say I'm a genius.

00:08:35.640 --> 00:08:38.280 align:middle line:84%
But it's in every
textbook of nutrition.

00:08:38.280 --> 00:08:40.860 align:middle line:84%
If you looked up
the glycemic index

00:08:40.860 --> 00:08:43.080 align:middle line:90%
of foods made of wheat flour--

00:08:43.080 --> 00:08:46.110 align:middle line:84%
that is, how high
blood sugar ranges over

00:08:46.110 --> 00:08:48.510 align:middle line:84%
90 minutes after
consuming a food,

00:08:48.510 --> 00:08:51.900 align:middle line:84%
you'll see that the foods with
the highest glycemic index,

00:08:51.900 --> 00:08:54.480 align:middle line:84%
the highest potential to
raise your blood sugar,

00:08:54.480 --> 00:08:57.210 align:middle line:90%
are all grains.

00:08:57.210 --> 00:09:00.570 align:middle line:84%
They're all products made of
wheat flour and corn starch

00:09:00.570 --> 00:09:05.040 align:middle line:84%
and corn meal and oats
and other related grains.

00:09:05.040 --> 00:09:09.420 align:middle line:84%
And so we've been told to
stack our diets heavily--

00:09:09.420 --> 00:09:12.540 align:middle line:84%
low in fat, right, rich
in healthy whole grains.

00:09:12.540 --> 00:09:14.340 align:middle line:84%
What we're being
told, in effect,

00:09:14.340 --> 00:09:17.760 align:middle line:84%
is follow a lifestyle
that guarantees

00:09:17.760 --> 00:09:21.600 align:middle line:84%
that you gain weight and
express higher blood sugars,

00:09:21.600 --> 00:09:23.850 align:middle line:84%
and you're on your way
to type 2 diabetes.

00:09:23.850 --> 00:09:26.210 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:09:26.210 --> 00:09:31.410 align:middle line:90%


00:09:31.410 --> 00:09:32.280 align:middle line:90%
Numerous changes.

00:09:32.280 --> 00:09:34.380 align:middle line:84%
One thing that has not
occurred is an increase

00:09:34.380 --> 00:09:35.520 align:middle line:90%
in the gluten content.

00:09:35.520 --> 00:09:36.720 align:middle line:90%
That's quite clear.

00:09:36.720 --> 00:09:38.400 align:middle line:84%
I mention that
because it's often

00:09:38.400 --> 00:09:40.620 align:middle line:84%
claimed that the source
of problems in wheat

00:09:40.620 --> 00:09:41.770 align:middle line:90%
is an increase in gluten.

00:09:41.770 --> 00:09:43.770 align:middle line:90%
And that's simply not true.

00:09:43.770 --> 00:09:45.492 align:middle line:90%
You and I are after truth.

00:09:45.492 --> 00:09:46.950 align:middle line:84%
And we don't want
to make up stuff.

00:09:46.950 --> 00:09:48.420 align:middle line:90%
So what is true?

00:09:48.420 --> 00:09:49.620 align:middle line:90%
What has been changed?

00:09:49.620 --> 00:09:52.320 align:middle line:84%
Well, we know lots of
things have been changed.

00:09:52.320 --> 00:09:55.140 align:middle line:84%
We know that the structure of
the gliadin protein in wheat

00:09:55.140 --> 00:09:58.410 align:middle line:84%
is very different today
than it was 40 years ago.

00:09:58.410 --> 00:10:01.110 align:middle line:84%
This is about a lot more than
celiac disease, as you know.

00:10:01.110 --> 00:10:03.200 align:middle line:90%
But just the form of gliadin--

00:10:03.200 --> 00:10:05.190 align:middle line:84%
people say gluten, but
it's really gliadin--

00:10:05.190 --> 00:10:08.400 align:middle line:84%
that provokes celiac
disease, the most potent form

00:10:08.400 --> 00:10:12.300 align:middle line:84%
of that protein is enriched
in modern strains of wheat

00:10:12.300 --> 00:10:16.660 align:middle line:84%
dramatically, compared
to wheat of 40 years ago.

00:10:16.660 --> 00:10:18.700 align:middle line:84%
There is something called
wheat germ agglutinin,

00:10:18.700 --> 00:10:21.810 align:middle line:84%
which is a very toxic protein
to your gastrointestinal tract.

00:10:21.810 --> 00:10:23.923 align:middle line:84%
It sounds like gluten,
but it's agglutinin.

00:10:23.923 --> 00:10:26.090 align:middle line:84%
It's unrelated, except it
comes from the same plant.

00:10:26.090 --> 00:10:28.600 align:middle line:90%


00:10:28.600 --> 00:10:32.610 align:middle line:84%
Farmers and geneticists
selected strains of wheat

00:10:32.610 --> 00:10:36.060 align:middle line:84%
that expressed greater
quantities of wheat germ

00:10:36.060 --> 00:10:40.050 align:middle line:84%
agglutinin because
it's also a pesticide.

00:10:40.050 --> 00:10:41.850 align:middle line:90%
It kills pests.

00:10:41.850 --> 00:10:43.740 align:middle line:90%
It drives off pests.

00:10:43.740 --> 00:10:46.590 align:middle line:84%
So they select strains with
higher wheat germ agglutinin

00:10:46.590 --> 00:10:49.800 align:middle line:84%
content, more toxic to the
human gastrointestinal tract.

00:10:49.800 --> 00:10:51.090 align:middle line:90%
It's a very potent toxin.

00:10:51.090 --> 00:10:53.250 align:middle line:84%
It's also a very highly
inflammatory protein,

00:10:53.250 --> 00:10:54.750 align:middle line:84%
the little small
quantities that are

00:10:54.750 --> 00:10:56.850 align:middle line:90%
absorbed into the bloodstream.

00:10:56.850 --> 00:10:58.920 align:middle line:84%
There's also something
called phytates

00:10:58.920 --> 00:11:01.080 align:middle line:90%
that are very rich in grains.

00:11:01.080 --> 00:11:04.110 align:middle line:84%
And these are very
potent binders

00:11:04.110 --> 00:11:07.230 align:middle line:84%
of minerals, particularly
calcium, magnesium, iron,

00:11:07.230 --> 00:11:08.250 align:middle line:90%
and zinc.

00:11:08.250 --> 00:11:10.530 align:middle line:84%
And so if I eat two slices
of whole wheat bread,

00:11:10.530 --> 00:11:14.670 align:middle line:84%
say, in a sandwich, 90%
of the iron in my diet

00:11:14.670 --> 00:11:18.320 align:middle line:84%
is prevented from
being absorbed.

00:11:18.320 --> 00:11:21.480 align:middle line:84%
And the phytates have
been enriched in grains

00:11:21.480 --> 00:11:26.140 align:middle line:84%
because they, likewise,
also provide pest resistance

00:11:26.140 --> 00:11:27.850 align:middle line:90%
to the wheat plant.

00:11:27.850 --> 00:11:29.250 align:middle line:90%
There's much more.

00:11:29.250 --> 00:11:31.345 align:middle line:84%
But in other words, it's
not just about gluten.

00:11:31.345 --> 00:11:33.720 align:middle line:84%
So I have to remind people
over and over and over again--

00:11:33.720 --> 00:11:35.460 align:middle line:84%
because they say, gluten--
the problem is gluten.

00:11:35.460 --> 00:11:36.627 align:middle line:90%
I'm going to go gluten-free.

00:11:36.627 --> 00:11:38.370 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to eat those
gluten-free foods.

00:11:38.370 --> 00:11:39.450 align:middle line:84%
So I'm trying to
encourage people

00:11:39.450 --> 00:11:41.160 align:middle line:84%
to get away from
that kind of thinking

00:11:41.160 --> 00:11:45.580 align:middle line:84%
and accept that the
entire package is corrupt.

00:11:45.580 --> 00:11:50.460 align:middle line:84%
The entire package of wheat and
other closely related grains

00:11:50.460 --> 00:11:53.400 align:middle line:84%
have a whole collection
of toxic components.

00:11:53.400 --> 00:11:54.600 align:middle line:90%
So don't think about gluten.

00:11:54.600 --> 00:11:57.630 align:middle line:84%
Think about the entire
package as being a flawed food

00:11:57.630 --> 00:11:58.610 align:middle line:90%
for human consumption.

